\section{Introduction}
The Basis Set Viewer is an enhancement to the unravel program. It allows
the user to view basis sets. A basis set is a set of linearly independent 
test paths. Each path in the basis set can not be formed as a combination of 
other paths in the basis set. Also, any path through the control flow graph 
can be formed as a combination of paths in the basis set.\cite{Poole95}
\section{Description}
The Basis Set Viewer (See Figure~\ref{fig:viewer}) includes the following:
\begin{enumerate} 
\item {\bf BUTTON BAR} - includes the following buttons:

	\begin{description}
        \item[\tt{Exit}] - exits the basis set viewer.
        \item[\tt{Select}] - allows for selection of a basis set and basis path.
        \item[\tt{Help}] - pops up a help file for the basis set viewer.
	\end{description}
 
\item {\bf STATUS BAR} - includes the following information:
 
	\begin{description}
        \item[\tt{File}] - the name of the file you are viewing.
        \item[\tt{Proc}] - the name of the function whose basis set is selected.
        \item[\tt{Path}] - the selected basis path in the selected basis set.
	\end{description}
 
\item {\bf SCROLL BAR} - used to scroll through the text of the file you have
			 selected.
 
\item {\bf TICK BAR} - used to locate highlighted text. May be used by 
	   itself or in combination with the scroll bar. If the highlighting 
	   is not visible either click on the tick bar or align the scroll bar 
	   with the ticks on the ticks bar. This will produce the highlighted text.
 
\end{enumerate} 

